    "description": "FUJIKURA COMPOSITES Inc. engages in the manufacture and sale of industrial rubber components in Japan, the United States, China, and internationally. The company manufactures and sells industrial materials, including pneumatic controllers, anti-vibration mounts, and peripherals; printing materials; electrical and electronic equipment; rescue and life-saving equipment; and carbon shafts for golf clubs. It also offers gas/water residential equipment, connecting parts, fire prevention sheets, and materials for speakers. In addition, the company provides check valves; automotive parts; calendared rubber; industrial equipment, including duct quarter vent rubber/butterfly, and BF and AB cylinders; calendared rubber, such as anti-vibration system, rubber-coated fabric, and pressure regulator; ultra-low hardness material and anti-vibration rubber products; paper roll airbags; and textile/material for clothing. Further, it offers emergency magnesium air batteries; blade protective sheets for wind turbine; various tapes for electric, cable connection, and repair; various molded products; cold shrink tubings; conservators; LIM products; dialyzers; proportional valves; latex products; disaster tents, air tents, and life rafts and jackets; graphite shaft for golf clubs; caravan shoes for climbing/trekking/hiking; footwear for walking and stream climbing; and climbing/bouldering shoes. The company was formerly known as Fujikura Rubber Ltd. and changed its name to FUJIKURA COMPOSITES Inc. in April 2019. FUJIKURA COMPOSITES Inc. was founded in 1901 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
